Stay at home
Only go outside for food, health reasons or work (but only if you cannot work from home)
If you go out, stay 2 metres (6ft) away from other people at all times
Wash your hands as soon as you get home
Do not meet others, even friends or family.
You can spread the virus even if you don’t have symptoms.

Bolivia’s land borders are closed and international flights are suspended until 15 April. There are currently no commercial options available to leave Bolivia.
UK special flight
Booking for UK special flights for British tourists, short term visitors and their direct dependants to return to the UK on 4 April has now closed. There are currently no further special flights organised from Bolivia.
This travel advice will be updated with further information on any future special flights and other options to leave Bolivia as soon as this is available. Sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British Embassy on Twitter and Facebook.
Future options
The British Embassy Bolivia is in contact with airlines, the Bolivian authorities and other governments to make sure commercial options for returning to the UK are available as soon as possible.
This travel advice will be updated when departure options become available.
If you cannot leave Bolivia at this time, you should:
follow the advice of local authorities, including local measures to help minimise your risk of exposure to coronavirus
find accommodation that’s suitable for your needs.
keep in regular contact with family and friends at home, so they know you are safe and well
observe the curfew and go out only when permitted
Help and support
If you need urgent consular assistance, you can contact the British Embassy on +591 2 2433424.
The Embassy cannot provide further information or advice about departure options over the phone. This page will be updated when departure options become available. To get the latest information, sign up for travel advice email alerts.
Further information
See additional advice on making travel plans to return to the UK, or what to do if you cannot depart immediately.
